<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n06027g"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n06" href="#n06027g">N06 (VI.B.11)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n06all.htm#n06027g"> 27(g)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> I hides smthg in featherbed</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">&lsquo;Joseph Sheridan Le Fanu&rsquo; This dagger she possessed herself of, taking it surreptitiously from its owner, Major Swan, because, in her own words,&mdash; <br>&ldquo;When I saw the dagger in the hands with which Lord Edward had striven in the last fatal struggle for life or death, I felt that it was not rightfully his who held it. I knew the spot in the front drawing-room where it was laid, and one evening I seized it, unobserved, and thrust it into my bosom; I returned to the company, where I had to sit for an hour. As soon as we got home I rushed up to the room which my sister and I occupied, and <mark>plunged it among the feathers of my bed</mark>, and for upwards of twelve years I lay every night upon the bed which contained my treasure. <small> Alfred Perceval Graves, <a name="ILMS2" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#ILMS2"><cite title="source">Irish Literary and Musical Studies</cite></a>, (1913) 61-2</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
